snippet.title: Lifetimegirl_2000's Story
snippet.description: ... Hello to everyone. My name is Janice and I am living with migraine. I started seeing my family physician back in the early 80's for headaches that were so horrible that I couldn't find the right words to describe them.I had been riding in my car when another car hit me from behind and jarred me really hard. No damage to the old car so we just agreeded to let it go.Very shortly after that is when the headaches started with fury. ... My doctors were great and immediently knew they were migraines. I started the regimine of a preventative, a med to kill an oncoming headache and then a back up med in case that didn't work. Then, if all else failed go to the ER.This has now been going on 3 decades. I've been to a neurologist and I am now at a Headache Wellness Center where they day I have genetic, chronic migraine.As of the last 122 days from today (01-02-09) I have had 38 migraines. I keep a diairy for them to keep track of my progress. I hope to meet other people with this horrible... ...

snippet.title: A painting from 2000
snippet.description: ... This painting is done in oils in 2000 when I was living in Portland OR and having a very hard time. I studied at a college of fine art instead of for a lucrative career so don't have a lot of income, and was doing an office job that barely covered my rent let alone medical, food, clothing, housing etc expenses. I couldn't afford to miss work and the doctors I saw dismissed my problems as they were difficult to figure out under the rules imposed by the insurance companies. So I worked with daily problems leaving permanent damage from not treating them. Most of my paintings are based on landscapes drawn from internal experience mixed with memory and impressions of places from my past. I didn't do this painting to illustrate a situation or make a point, it was more an explosion of a lot of pain and frustration over time. I don't really like to talk about meaning or symbolism in my work, I feel if it doesn't speak for itself then it's not done... meaning is in the ... ...
